<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="565" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,401,1149]" pageId="1" pageNumber="565">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,401,426]" pageId="1" pageNumber="565">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body elongate, abdomen laterally nearly parallel (
<figureCitation box="[842,907,401,426]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,2005,2027]" captionTargetBox="[184,1399,185,2004]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[184,1400,185,2082]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Flexitibia orientalis sp. nov., ♂, habitus. Scale bar of 1 = 2.52 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230496/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="565">
Fig. 
<number box="[894,907,402,426]" pageId="1" pageNumber="565" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Head slightly shorter than pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1354,1422,401,426]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[203,1364,212,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[180,1407,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 10. Flexitibia orientalis sp. nov. ♂. 2, head and pronotum, antennae removed; 3, apical part of hind tibia; 4, apical part of abdomen; 5, 6, pygophore; 7, paramere; 8, phallus; 9, 10, phallosoma. 5, 10, ventral view; 2, 4, 6, 8, lateral view; 9, dorsal view. Scale bar of 2 = 0.87 mm; of 3, 7 = 0.31 mm; of 4 = 0.73 mm; of 5, 6 = 0.34 mm; of 8 – 10 = 0.31 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230497/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="565">
Fig. 
<number box="[1406,1422,402,426]" pageId="1" pageNumber="565" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
), with a spine behind base of antennal tubercle; postocular area subequal to anteocular in length, transversely impressed between eyes; first antennal segment nearly as long as hind tibia; first rostral segment distinctly longer than second and third segments combined (
<figureCitation box="[632,701,509,534]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[203,1364,212,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[180,1407,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 10. Flexitibia orientalis sp. nov. ♂. 2, head and pronotum, antennae removed; 3, apical part of hind tibia; 4, apical part of abdomen; 5, 6, pygophore; 7, paramere; 8, phallus; 9, 10, phallosoma. 5, 10, ventral view; 2, 4, 6, 8, lateral view; 9, dorsal view. Scale bar of 2 = 0.87 mm; of 3, 7 = 0.31 mm; of 4 = 0.73 mm; of 5, 6 = 0.34 mm; of 8 – 10 = 0.31 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230497/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="565">
Fig. 
<number box="[684,701,510,534]" pageId="1" pageNumber="565" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotum discally slightly bulging and conspicuously anteriorly declining, lateral margin nearly straight; collar processes obtuse; anterior pronotal lobe much smaller than posterior; disk of posterior lobe not depressed but anteriorly feebly bulgy, and two sides without lateral sulci (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,2005,2027]" captionTargetBox="[184,1399,185,2004]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[184,1400,185,2082]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Flexitibia orientalis sp. nov., ♂, habitus. Scale bar of 1 = 2.52 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230496/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="565">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,164,618,642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="565" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); lateral pronotal angles produced laterally, short spine-shaped, with a small denticle behind it; posterior and posterolateral margins nearly straight; scutellum somewhat long and subtriangular, apex posteriorly produced. Legs slender; femora apically with a pair of small spines; fore legs somewhat thickened, apical part of fore tibiae bent; apex of fore tibia with a small tubercle (
<figureCitation box="[661,744,725,750]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 16. 11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[284,1287,211,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[284,1302,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 16. 11. Camptibia obscura Cai &amp; Tomokuni; 12. Rihirbus sinicus Hsiao &amp; Ren; 13. Brassivola hystrix Distant; 14. Flexitibia orientalis sp. nov.; 15. Agyrius watanabeorum Ishikawa; 16. Endochus cingalensis Stål. 11 – 16, fore leg. 11 – 16, lateral view. Scale bar of 11 – 13, 16 = 2.00 mm; of 14 – 15 = 1.33 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230498/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="565">
Fig. 
<number box="[713,744,726,750]" pageId="1" pageNumber="565" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Fore wing membrane area large, inner cell longer than outer cell at base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
